179876.name: Annual consumption-based CO2 emissions (per capita)
179876.description: Annual consumption-based emissions of carbon dioxide (CO2), measured in tonnes per person. Consumption-based emissions are national or regional emissions which have been adjusted for trade (i.e. territorial/production emissions minus emissions embedded in exports, plus emissions embedded in imports). If a country's consumption-based emissions are higher than its production emissions it is a net importer of carbon dioxide. Consumption-based CO2 emissions have been converted by Our World in Data from tonnes of carbon to tonnes of CO2 using a conversion factor of 3.664.

The Global Carbon Budget dataset is available at https://doi.org/10.18160/gcp-2021 and https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5569235.

Full references:

Global Carbon Project. (2021). Supplemental data of Global Carbon Project 2021 (1.0) [Data set]. Global Carbon Project. https://doi.org/10.18160/gcp-2021.

Andrew, Robbie M., & Peters, Glen P. (2021). The Global Carbon Project's fossil CO2 emissions dataset [Data set]. Zenodo. https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5569235.

Our World in Data have renamed the category "bunker fuels" as "International transport" for improved clarity, which includes emissions from international aviation and shipping.

Population figures are sourced from Gapminder (v6), HYDE (v3.2), United Nations Population Division (2019). Links: https://www.gapminder.org/data/documentation/gd003/; https://population.un.org/wpp/Download/Standard/Population/; https://dataportaal.pbl.nl/downloads/HYDE/

Consumption-based CO2 emissions have been constructed by the Global Carbon Project using the methodology described in:

Peters, GP, Minx, JC, Weber, CL and Edenhofer, O 2011. Growth in emission transfers via international trade from 1990 to 2008. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences 108, 8903-8908. http://www.pnas.org/content/108/21/8903.abstract
